refsect1.para:
Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.


    &opt_h;
    &opt_help;



        display help message and terminate





    &opt_version;



        display version information and terminate





    &opt_q;
    &opt_quiet;



        do not display warning messages





    &opt_v;
    &opt_verbose;



        display concise intermediate messages





    &opt_f;
    &opt_freevar;



        do not replace free variables in the LPE with dummy values





    &opt_y;
    &opt_dummy;



        replace free variables in the LPE with dummy values (default)





    &opt_u;
    &opt_unused-data;



        do not remove unused parts of the data specification





    &opt_c;
    &opt_vector;



        store state in a vector (fastest, default)





    &opt_r;
    &opt_tree;



        store state in a tree (for memory efficiency)





    &opt_l;
    &opt_max;=NUM



        explore at most NUM states





    &opt_d;
    &opt_deadlock;
    &opt_deadlock-detect;



        detect deadlocks (i.e. for every deadlock a message is printed)





    &opt_e;
    &opt_deadlock-trace;



         write trace to each deadlock state to a file





    &opt_D;
    &opt_detect;=NAME



         detect actions from NAME* (i.e. print a message for every occurence)





    &opt_t;
    &opt_trace;=NAME



         write trace to each state that is reached with an action from NAME* to a file





    &opt_p;
    &opt_priority;=NAME



         give priority to action NAME (i.e. if it is possible to
         execute an action NAME in some state, than make it the only
         executable action from that state)





    &opt_m;
    &opt_monitor;



         print detailed status of generation





    &opt_R;
    &opt_rewriter;=NAME



         use rewriter NAME (default 'inner3')





    &opt_aut;



         force &outfile; to be in the aut format (implies
                        &opt_no-info;, see below)  





    &opt_svc;



         force &outfile; to be in the svc format





    &opt_no-info;



         do not add state information to &outfile;
